description: aUSDC represents USDC supplied to the AAVE protocol. By depositing aUSDC into Pendle, users can earn a fixed APY on your aUSDC. The yield is generated by forfeiting the right to claim aUSDC's variable APY in the AAVE protocol. Withdrawing will become available after the maturity date. If you want to withdraw before the maturity date you can do so in Pendle's web app.

weETH is an LRT (Liquidity Restaking Token). By depositing weETH into Pendle, users can earn a fixed APY on their weETH. The yield is generated by forfeiting the right to claim weETH's APY and any airdrops. Withdrawing will become available after the maturity date. If you want to withdraw before the maturity date you can do so in Pendle's web app.

USDC is a 100% backed digital dollar minted by Circle and is always redeemable 1:1 for US dollars. By depositing USDC into AAVE, users can earn a variable APY on the USDC. The yield is generated by depositing USDC in AAVE's lending markets and automatically accrued in your account .

USDT is a 100% backed digital dollar minted by iFinex and is always redeemable 1:1 for US dollars. By depositing USDT into AAVE, users can earn a variable APY on the USDT. The yield is generated by depositing USDT in AAVE's lending markets and is automatically accrued in your account.

USDC is a 100% backed digital dollar minted by Circle and is always redeemable 1:1 for US dollars. By depositing USDC into AAVE, users can earn a variable APY on the USDC. The yield is generated by depositing USDC in AAVE's lending markets and is automatically accrued in your account.

wETH is the wrapped version of the Ethereum token. By depositing wETH into AAVE, users can earn a variable APY on the wETH. The yield is generated by depositing wETH in AAVE's lending markets and is automatically accrued in your account.

DAI is a multi-collateral-backed stablecoin managed by MakerDAO that attempts to maintain a value of $1.00 USD. By depositing DAI into AAVE, users can earn a variable APY on the DAI. The yield is generated by depositing DAI in AAVE's lending markets and automatically accrued in your account.

DAI is a multi-collateral-backed stablecoin managed by MakerDAO that attempts to maintain a value of $1.00 USD. The DSR is a special module in the MakerDAO smart contract system that allows DAI holders to receive a share of the revenue earned by MakerDAO. The yield is generated by depositing DAI in the DSR and automatically accrued in your account.

ENA is the governance token for Ethena, a DeFi protocol focused on creating a synthetic dollar (USDe). By depositing ENA into Pendle, users can earn a fixed APY on their ENA. The yield is generated by forfeiting the right to claim ENA's season 2 points. Withdrawing will become available after the maturity date. If you want to withdraw before the maturity date you can do so in Pendle's web app.

USDe is a delta-neutral synthetic dollar created by Ethena Labs. By depositing USDe into Pendle, users can earn a fixed APY on their USDe. The yield is generated by forfeiting the right to claim USDe's season 2 points. Withdrawing will become available after the maturity date. If you want to withdraw before the maturity date you can do so in Pendle's web app.

Lido is the leading Ethereum staking pool. By depositing ETH into Lido, users can earn a variable APY on their ETH. The yield is generated by staking the user's ETH and claiming the native Ethereum staking yield. The yield is automatically accrued in your account.
